he is old he will not depart from it.&quot; </div><div class="t m59f x86 hc ybe ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">According to Cynthia Tobias of Learning Styles Unlimited, the original </div><div class="t m5b1 x86 hc y8fa ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Hebrew of the verb translated &quot;train&quot; is used uniquely in Proverbs 22:6. It </div><div class="t m72c x16 hc y2de ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">referred to the clearing out of the mouth of a newly born baby, and meant, </div><div class="t m6d2 x86 hc y1d ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;Create an environment for life.&quot; </div><div class="t m202 x72 hc y8fb ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Thus, we could understand the verse to mean, &quot;Create an environment </div><div class="t m739 x16 hc y2e0 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">for life for a child, in keeping with his gifts or bent, and when he is old he </div><div class="t m73a x16 hc y10d ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">will not depart from it.&quot; </div><div class="t m460 x17 h24 y8fc ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What relationships between children and parents do the fol-</div><div class="t m245 x16 h24 y8fd ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">lowing passages speak of? </div><div class="t m5be x17 h24 y8fe ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Prov. 10:1 </div><div class="t m1c x47 h24 y8fe ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m4b0 x5c h24 y8fe ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m1f4 x17 h24 y8ff ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Prov. 27:11 </div><div class="t m1c x4a h24 y8ff ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m4b0 x5c h24 y8ff ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m200 x17 h24 y900 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Prov. </div><div class="t m5e3 xa3 hc y901 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">28:7 </div><div class="t m1c x58 hc y901 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m4b0 x5c hc y901 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m3f2 x46 hc y902 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Prov. 29:15 </div><div class="t m1c x4d hc y2e9 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m4b0 x5c hc y2e9 ff3 fs7 fc0 sc0 l